<p>At the same date, John Edward was to be found living with newly-wed wife Theresa and his brother Richard
    [II] at 56 Union Street, Lower Broughton. This was about three-quarters of a mile from Mary Ann's lodgings as the crow
    flew. They stated their ages as 25 (Theresa), 23 (John) and 19 (Richard), although John was still a few months short of his
    23rd birthday. This was the first census at which householders were required to complete their own forms, so here
    is the document in John's own hand and signed by him. It looks as if, quite understandably, he struggled a bit with the
    bureaucratic aspects of putting things in the right boxes.</p>
	
