<p>The table of Lower Broughton Malone families and addresses below also lists the children
    which had been produced by the clan by census day 1911. The signs were that if John and Theresa's grandchildren were
    ever - in the future - to seek out a lost second cousin or two on their grandmother's side, they would probably have a
    large pool to choose from. On their grandfather's side of course, they have me and all my first cousins, descended
    from Richard [II] Noonan. The "Malone Quarter" was also fairly close to Greengate, where St Peter's Catholic church was located.
    This was convenient, for it was	longer-established than St Boniface's and probably offered more services.</p>

